title: Ashley, Barnes top area runners
text: Ashley, Barnes top area runners Niceville won the girls title and Maclay the boys in the Panhandle Championships cross country meet on Saturday. Posted Oct. 12, 2015 at 5:26 PM Updated at 5:34 PM Posted Oct. 12, 2015 at 5:26 PM Updated at 5:34 PM MARIANNA — Niceville won the girls title and Maclay the boys in the Panhandle Championships cross country meet on Saturday. Caroline Willis of Maclay was the girls individual winner, covering the 5,000-meter course in 19 minutes, 9.47 seconds. Michaela Ashley of Arnold was the top area finisher placing 13th in 20:55.70. No area schools were a factor in the team competition in either division. James McClure of Maclay bested the boys field in 16:43.37. The top area runner was Garry Barnes of Cottondale, who placed 11th in 17:10.76. Results follow. Girls team: 1. Niceville 45, 2. Maclay 68, 3. Choctawhatchee 101, 4. Crestview 143, 5. Pace 155, 6.
